{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1f76bd66-a9e8-48d3-940e-beea7f1fbaf1","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke`) becomes the MTP `--filter` syntax, which uses **forward-slash selectors**:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n#                          ↓  becomes  ↓\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nMTP uses `/` instead of `&` for AND. The `~` (contains) operator still works.\n\n### 2. Trait filtering property name\n\nIn MTP, traits are exposed as **`Category`** (same name you used), so that part is fine. The full equivalent:\n\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### Quick reference\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|--------|-----|\n| `&` (AND) | `/` |\n| `\\|` (OR) | `\\|` (same) |\n| `!` (NOT) | `!` (same) |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (same) |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` (same) |\n\nSo for your CI, just replace `&` with `/` in the filter string.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6d7e2925-10f5-4edf-8a33-6cea009e7550","outputTokens":349},"id":"33429c88-dee8-4a6a-8341-8c6dd729075c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:38.777Z","parentId":"5e6112ff-4a30-44e6-b55c-0597e4860aa9"}
